                                                                                                                                    <p>By no means should "downgrading" your car be seen as a bad thing. Especially in this day and age, consumers are becoming increasingly conscious of many critical factors when purchasing a car, <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/should-you-buy-or-lease-a-car/" target="_blank">whether leasing or buying outright</a>.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 20 Sep 2025 19:30:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/downgrades-that-might-be-upgrades/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[10 Affordable Laptop Workspace Upgrades Under $20]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/affordable-laptop-workspace-upgrades-under-20/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ismar Hrnjicevic]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/52844692712_16be54b0a6_o.jpg" length="269" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[laptops]]></category><category><![CDATA[Productivity]]></category><category><![CDATA[headphones]]></category><category><![CDATA[mouse]]></category><category><![CDATA[Mechanical Keyboards]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Even cheap accessories can make a huge difference.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If you work primarily off a laptop, you’re likely already aware of the productivity and comfort benefits that a few small gadgets can provide. The best part is that many of them can make a meaningful difference without draining your wallet.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 20 Sep 2025 19:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/affordable-laptop-workspace-upgrades-under-20/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Hate the Windows 11 Widgets Panel? Here's How to Completely Get Rid of It]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/hate-the-windows-11-widgets-panel-heres-how-to-completely-get-rid-of-it/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Aman Kumar]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/windows_11_widgets3-1.png" length="2598" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows 11]]></category><category><![CDATA[Microsoft]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Until Microsoft improves the widget panel, you can disable it completely.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The widgets panel on Windows 11 gives you quick access to information like news, weather, stocks, and more. However, I really don't like it, as it takes up a good amount of taskbar space and often interferes with my workflow by popping up unexpectedly. If you also don't find the widgets panel helpful, here's how you can disable it completely.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 20 Sep 2025 18:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/hate-the-windows-11-widgets-panel-heres-how-to-completely-get-rid-of-it/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[I Disabled Windows Startup Apps—Here's How Much Faster My PC Boots]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/disabling-startup-apps-improve-boot-time/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Shan Abdul]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/the-windows-10-startup-screen-in-the-settings-app.jpg" length="145" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><category><![CDATA[PC Optimization]]></category><category><![CDATA[Hardware]]></category><category><![CDATA[Windows]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Minor tweak, major payoff!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>If your device takes ages to boot, and you blame it on its age, you’re mistaken. I used to think the same until I found the real culprit—too many apps loading at startup. Turning off unnecessary apps made my device boot faster. I applied this change on two devices, and here’s the difference it made.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 20 Sep 2025 18:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/disabling-startup-apps-improve-boot-time/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[This Hybrid Became the Benchmark for Longevity]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/this-hybrid-became-the-benchmark-for-longevity/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Adam Gray]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/toyota-prius-2012-hd-d90892a01bb68286b64d76c90f129020612fedb89.jpg" length="285" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Automotive]]></category><category><![CDATA[Hybrid Cars]]></category><category><![CDATA[Toyota]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            The first hybrid showed it’s built to last, setting the bar for how tough a car can be.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p><a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/tag/hybrid-cars/" target="_blank">Hybrids</a> might seem tricky with two power sources under the hood, but when done right they’re actually easier to live with than a regular gas car.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 20 Sep 2025 17:01:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/this-hybrid-became-the-benchmark-for-longevity/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Missing Launchpad in macOS Tahoe? Here 3 Ways to Replace It]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/replace-launchpad-in-macos-tahoe-here-are-your-options/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Andy Betts]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/appguard-launchpad-replacement-on-macos-tahoe-1.jpg" length="410" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Mac]]></category><category><![CDATA[macOS]]></category><category><![CDATA[Apps & Web Apps]]></category><category><![CDATA[macOS Tahoe]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            You can't bring Launchpad back, but these are the next best things.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>One of the main features that was removed from macOS Tahoe was the app launcher, Launchpad. A lot of people didn't use it and won't miss it, but for people like me who used it every day, it's a big loss. Unfortunately, there's no way to bring back Launchpad, but there are other options you can use instead.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 20 Sep 2025 16:30:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/replace-launchpad-in-macos-tahoe-here-are-your-options/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Don't Forget to Change These 5 BIOS Settings When Dual-Booting Windows and Linux]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/change-these-bios-settings-when-dual-booting-windows-and-linux/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Dibakar Ghosh]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/laptop-with-the-asus-bios-screen.jpg" length="530" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Linux]]></category><category><![CDATA[computer hardware]]></category><category><![CDATA[PC Optimization]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Five settings, a couple of minutes, and zero more dual-boot headaches
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Are you dual-booting Windows and Linux but struggling with a clunky boot process and system conflicts? Wondering why your setup feels less smooth than promised? Well, here are five essential BIOS settings that, when changed, can potentially fix these headaches immediately.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Sat, 20 Sep 2025 16:15:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/change-these-bios-settings-when-dual-booting-windows-and-linux/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Don't Be Fooled by the Latest Gimmick in PC Gaming Hardware]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/your-motherboard-has-gaming-focused-usb-ports-but-do-they-actually-matter/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Ismar Hrnjicevic]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/rsz_1img20250916144621.png" length="1981" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[PC Gaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[mouse]]></category><category><![CDATA[Keyboards]]></category><category><![CDATA[Online Gaming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
